        <p>https:Ramanagara, known as the "Land of Seven Hills" and famous for the Sholay movie shooting, offers popular tourist spots including Ramadevara Betta, Savandurga Hill, Janapada Loka, and Mekedatu. Other key attractions include Kanva Reservoir, SRS Hills, Chunchi Falls, and the silk cocoon market. 
Here is a list of top tourist places in and around Ramanagara:
Hills and Trekking
Ramadevara Betta: Famous for a 1000-year-old temple and the vulture sanctuary.
Savandurga Hill: One of the largest monolith hills in Asia, ideal for trekking.
SRS Hills (Sri Revanna Siddeshwara Betta): A sacred hill with a Shiva temple.
Kabbaladurga: A fort located on a hill popular for night trekking.
Sholay Shooting HillTop: The location where the classic movie Sholay was filmed. 
Nature and Sightseeing
Mekedatu: A scenic spot where the Kaveri River flows through a deep gorge.
Chunchi Falls: A waterfall surrounded by rocky landscapes near Kanakapura.
Kanva Reservoir: A calm, artificial lake suitable for picnics.
Manchanabele Dam: Known for its scenic water views.
Arkavati River: A relaxing, scenic spot. 
Culture and Shopping
Janapada Loka: A museum displaying the folk culture of Karnataka.
Channapatna: Known as the "Toy Town of India" for its traditional lacquer wooden toys.
Ramanagara Silk Cocoon Market: One of the largest silk markets in India. 
Religious Sites
Kengal Anjaneya Swamy Temple: A well-known temple.
Navaneetha Krishna Temple: Located in the Ramanagara district.
Doddamaluru Aprameya Temple: A historic temple. 
Other Major Hills (Seven Hills)
Yatirajagiri, Shivaramagiri, Somagiri, Krishnagiri, Sidilakallu Betta, and Jalasiddeshawara Betta. </p> 
