    <h1> Tourist places in my hometown Ramanagara </h1> 
    <div class="tourist-spot"> 
        <h2> Ramadevara Betta </h2> 
        <img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/dyiffrkzh/image/upload/c_fill,f_auto,fl_progressive.strip_profile,g_center,h_400,q_auto,w_700/v1692702068/bbj/gte5uudgqspoituo79da.jpg" alt="Ramadevara Betta"> 
        <p> Ramadevara Betta is renowned for its ancient temple dedicated to Lord Rama and its status as a vulture sanctuary. The hill offers panoramic views and is a popular spot for trekking enthusiasts. Visitors can explore the temple, enjoy the natural beauty, and observe the diverse birdlife in the area. </p> 
    </div> 

    <div class="tourist-spot"> 
        <h2> Savandurga Hill </h2> 
        <img src="https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcS5K3Gp04wCSAsuFlWkKlDMkM_v_UYlPQaCyA&s" alt="Savandurga Hill"> 
        <p> Savandurga Hill is one of the largest monolith hills in Asia, making it a significant attraction for trekkers and nature lovers. The hill features two peaks, Karigudda (Black Hill) and Biligudda (White Hill), each offering unique trekking experiences. The area is also home to various flora and fauna, making it a great spot for wildlife enthusiasts. </p> 
    </div> 
